Epicurus: 342-270 B.C. Owing to the universality of belief in the gods, Epicurus did not deny their existence, but maintained they had no concern for the world: verbis reliquit deos, re sustulit (Cio. ibid. 1. 30. 85). He regarded Nature as a blind unconscious force governing the movement of atoms. Cf. Tert. Apol. 47. 6.
